Can a warm and supportive adult protect against mental health problems amongst adolescents exposed to adversity? A twin-differences study

Sarah E. Stock

This document was last edited on 2023-10-04 using R version 4.2.3

1 Preparation

Load the packages

library(psych)    # for descriptives
library(polycor)  # for between pair correlations
library(geepack)  # for gee regressions
library(ggplot2)  # for graphs
library(dplyr)    # for grammar to allow %>% 
library(ggeffects)# for gee graphs
library(emmeans)  # for gee graphs
library(ggpubr)   # for combining the ggplots together
library(stringr)  # for mutate function
library(data.table) # for set names function
library("Hmisc") # for within pair correlations
library(tidyr)
library(gtsummary)
options(scipen=999) #prevents scientific notation

Prepare variables (after bringing in data)

erisk$behave5 <- NA; erisk$behave5 <- apply(erisk[,c("totagge5","totdele5")],1, sum, na.rm=F) #behavioural problems eldest twin (5)
erisk$behave12 <- NA; erisk$behave12 <- apply(erisk[,c("totagge12","totdele12")],1, sum, na.rm=F) #behavioural problems eldest (12)
erisk$behavy5 <- NA; erisk$behavy5 <- apply(erisk[,c("totaggy5","totdely5")],1, sum, na.rm=F) #behavioural problems youngest twin (5)
erisk$behavy12 <- NA; erisk$behavy12 <- apply(erisk[,c("totaggy12","totdely12")],1, sum, na.rm=F) #behavioural problems youngest twin (12)

erisk$matwarmthe <- NA; erisk$matwarmthe <- apply(erisk[,c("warme5","warme10")],1, mean, na.rm=T) #maternal warmth average eldest twin
erisk$matwarmthy <- NA; erisk$matwarmthy <- apply(erisk[,c("warmy5","warmy10")],1, mean, na.rm=T) #maternal warmth average youngest twin

erisk$aces1plus <- NA; erisk$aces1plus <- ifelse(erisk$acese512<1,0,1) #binary ACE variable (one or more ACE)
table(erisk$aces1plus)

4 Analysis

Create dataset for analysis, to include only those with experience of 1 or more ACE. Following this, standardise all the outcome and exposure variables

erisk_1ace <- subset(erisk, aces1plus==1)
   #Standardise outcomes
erisk_1ace$totemoe12sd <- scale(erisk_1ace$totemoe12)
erisk_1ace$totemoy12sd <- scale(erisk_1ace$totemoy12)
erisk_1ace$behave12sd <- scale(erisk_1ace$behave12)
erisk_1ace$behavy12sd <- scale(erisk_1ace$behavy12)
erisk_1ace$PH_Esd <- scale(erisk_1ace$PH_E)
erisk_1ace$PH_Ysd <- scale(erisk_1ace$PH_Y)
   #Standardise exposures
erisk_1ace$matwarmthesd <- scale(erisk_1ace$matwarmthe)
erisk_1ace$matwarmthysd <- scale(erisk_1ace$matwarmthy)
erisk_1ace$adultec12sd <- scale(erisk_1ace$adultec12)
erisk_1ace$adultyc12sd <- scale(erisk_1ace$adultyc12)
   #Covariates
erisk_1ace$totemoe5sd <- scale(erisk_1ace$totemoe5)

erisk_1ace$behave5sd <- scale(erisk_1ace$behave5)
erisk_1ace$behavy5sd <- scale(erisk_1ace$behavy5)

Calculate mean and twin difference scores based off standardised measures

erisk_1ace$matwarm_mean <- NA; erisk_1ace$matwarm_mean <- rowMeans(erisk_1ace[,c("matwarmthesd", "matwarmthysd")])
erisk_1ace$adult_mean <- NA; erisk_1ace$adult_mean <- rowMeans(erisk_1ace[,c("adultec12sd", "adultyc12sd")])
erisk_1ace$emo5_mean <- NA; erisk_1ace$emo5_mean <- rowMeans(erisk_1ace[,c("totemoe5sd", "totemoy5sd")])
erisk_1ace$beh5_mean <- NA; erisk_1ace$beh5_mean <- rowMeans(erisk_1ace[,c("behave5sd", "behavy5sd")])
erisk_1ace$matwarm_diff1 <- NA; erisk_1ace$matwarm_diff1 <- erisk_1ace$matwarmthesd - erisk_1ace$matwarm_mean
erisk_1ace$adult_diff1 <- NA; erisk_1ace$adult_diff1 <- erisk_1ace$adultec12sd - erisk_1ace$adult_mean
erisk_1ace$emo5_diff1 <- NA; erisk_1ace$emo5_diff1 <- erisk_1ace$totemoe5sd - erisk_1ace$emo5_mean
erisk_1ace$beh5_diff1 <- NA; erisk_1ace$beh5_diff1 <- erisk_1ace$behave5sd - erisk_1ace$beh5_mean

MZ twin analysis - adjusted (RQ2)

   #Maternal warmth & emotional problems
test <- subset(erisk_1ace, zygosity==1 & !is.na(totemoe12sd) & !is.na(matwarm_mean))
geemodel <- geeglm(scale(totemoe12sd) ~ scale(matwarm_mean) + scale(matwarm_diff1) + emo5_mean + emo5_diff1,
                   data=test, id=familyid, corstr="exchangeable")
mw_emo <- tidy(geemodel, conf.int = TRUE, conf.level = 0.95) [c(3),c(2,6,7)]; mw_emo <- as.data.frame(mw_emo)
   #Maternal warmth & behavioural problems
test <- subset(erisk_1ace, zygosity==1 & !is.na(behave12sd) & !is.na(matwarm_mean))
geemodel <- geeglm(scale(behave12sd) ~ scale(matwarm_mean) + scale(matwarm_diff1) + beh5_mean + beh5_diff1,
                   data=test, id=familyid, corstr="exchangeable")

Estimate reduction in effect size from phenotypic to DZ & MZ (all twin - at) estimates & from phenotypic to MZ estimates. Note: Proportional decrease = (Original Number - New Number)/Original Number

# Rename variables in model1 and model3
setnames(model1, old = c("model", "pf", "outcome", "estimate", "conf.low", "conf.high"), new = c("model", "pf", "outcome", "estimate_ph", "conf.low_ph", "conf.high_ph"), skip_absent = T)
setnames(model2, old = c("model", "pf", "outcome", "estimate", "conf.low", "conf.high"), new = c("model", "pf", "outcome", "estimate_at", "conf.low_at", "conf.high_at"), skip_absent = T)
setnames(model3, old = c("model", "pf", "outcome", "estimate", "conf.low", "conf.high"), new = c("model", "pf", "outcome", "estimate_mz", "conf.low_mz", "conf.high_mz"), skip_absent = T)

model1_ai <- model1[c(4,5,6),]
model2_mw <- model2[c(1,2,3),]
model2_ai <- model2[c(4,5,6),]
model3_mw <- model3[c(1,2,3),]
model3_ai <- model3[c(4,5,6),]

#all twin comparison table - Maternal warmth
comparison_table_mw_at <- merge(model1_mw, model2_mw, by="outcome")
comparison_table_ai_at <- merge(model1_ai, model2_ai, by="outcome")
#mz comparison table
comparison_table_mw_mz <- merge(model1_mw, model3_mw, by="outcome")
comparison_table_ai_mz <- merge(model1_ai, model3_ai, by="outcome")

# Derive variable indexing reduction in effects from phenotypic to MZ analysis
#all twin
comparison_table_mw_at$percent_decrease_at <- (comparison_table_mw_at$estimate_ph - comparison_table_mw_at$estimate_at) / comparison_table_mw_at$estimate_ph
comparison_table_ai_at$percent_decrease_at <- (comparison_table_ai_at$estimate_ph - comparison_table_ai_at$estimate_at) / comparison_table_ai_at$estimate_ph
#mz twin
comparison_table_mw_mz$percent_decrease_mz <- (comparison_table_mw_mz$estimate_ph - comparison_table_mw_mz$estimate_mz) / comparison_table_mw_mz$estimate_ph
comparison_table_ai_mz$percent_decrease_mz <- (comparison_table_ai_mz$estimate_ph - comparison_table_ai_mz$estimate_mz) / comparison_table_ai_mz$estimate_ph

# Average percentage decrease
# AT analysis - Maternal warmth
